author: danielsh
msg: Further simplify use of 'subprocess'.  Two uses of .Popen remain.
(subprocess.check_output): Provide a sufficient replacement for Python 2.6,
when not available in the library.
(compare_changes, clean_dist, move_to_dist): Use check_output().  This way,
non-zero exit code with no stderr would still be detected as an error.
